I might make this, and it is probably delicious. Just be aware that it has been tinkered with. Authentic pasta Bolognese uses only beef (ground skirt steak, actually), no cream (reduced whole milk instead), and is very light on the tomatoes--5 Tb. paste, at the most. And it traditionally served with tagliatelle. It does not use Parmigiano-Reggiano either, though I suppose it could, since it does come from the same region. We Americans just love to gussy things up and heap on the butterfat.

