Rating: 0
This is a great recipe. I've made it several times now, with subtle variations each time based on available ingredients. For the most part, I followed as is, using half the suggested oil and omitting the carrot (although I intend to try it). The difference in each time i've made it has been the availability of pancetta and/or orecchiette. I substituted lean bacon for the pancetta when i couldn't find it, and medium shells when I couldn't find the orecchiette. Shells or orecchiette are definitely the way to go because the rich meaty sauce kind of fills into the pasta and its a thing of beauty. As others have suggested I also added a few things to spice it up and make it feel like my own. I chose to include garlic powder and oregano while the meat is simmering, and dried basil after adding the crushed tomatoes (You can also find basil seasoned crushed tomatoes instead). The dry red wine is kind of important to stick to, I once used what I had, which was just a sweeter california red table wine and it just wasnt the same. On a side note, if you can find pancetta, use it! Using bacon was just fine, but let me tell you, when I actually found pancetta it turned this dish into something magical. Last note is that this recipe makes a nice size pot, but don't worry it will go quick, and it might be even better the next day. Thank you so much for sharing this recipe, I'm very thankful and happy to store this into my repertoire!

